<br>
Can Project Lightning be bought, or does it still have to be researched?<br>
<br>
---<br>
Kimaya Silverbark<br>
<br>
&quot;So, what would happen if I took a chunk of lava, a lightstone, and a clump of dough, and combined it all into a big lump and dropped it in an oven...?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umheddik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mheddik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/02 8:22:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1052.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> That name</span><hr size=1> Project Lightning sounds like a cool codename Benjamin Franklin might have used for his kite-flying experiment. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
