&lt;Starspun&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeneteth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deneteth1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/02 10:41:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1052.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: That name</span><hr size=1> If the researchable spells can be bought in Luclin it's not in Shadowheavens nor Sanctu Seru... if someone knows where I would be interested even if I thinks it will be last resort, so far I've never felt short on my capability even when missing some research spells.<br>
<br>
And no, project lightning can't be found in the Firiona Vie outpost, it's research only. From what I remember there are some high level quests (for the concussion spell as an example) that start in FV but that's pretty it.<br>
<br>
